<resources>
    <!--
    - Main Apptentive Styling item info

    - Have a style named "ApptentiveThemeOverride" in your styles.xml file to override Apptentive styles
    - Items defined in this style will ONLY affect Apptentive interactions

    - We disable the android:background style for Apptentive interaction styling
    - It causes some unexpected issues for some Views
    - You can re-enable this within ApptentiveThemeOverride

    - Material Color info: https://material.io/blog/android-material-theme-color

    Dialogs:
    - Dialog background color uses colorSurface
    - Dialog color on background (title and message text) uses colorOnSurface
    - Dialog buttons text color uses colorSecondary
        - Override with apptentiveTextColorDialogTextButton
    - Dialog title has an alpha of .90 by default
        - Override with apptentiveHeaderAlpha
    - Dialog message has an alpha of .75 by default
        - Override with apptentiveSubheaderAlpha

    Use Love Dialog header image:

    - Love Dialog small title header image example start -
    - This is positioned before the title text -
    - Set through style apptentiveLoveDialogTitleImageStyle
    <style name="Custom.LoveDialog.Title.Image">
        <item name="android:src">@mipmap/ic_launcher</item> <- Your image (preferably app logo)
        <item name="android:maxWidth">40dp</item> <- minWidth/maxWidth to size
        <item name="android:maxHeight">40dp</item> <- minHeight/maxHeight to size
        <item name="android:adjustViewBounds">true</item> <- Helps with image resizing
    </style>
    - Love Dialog small title header image example end -

    - Love Dialog large header image example start -
    - This is positioned above the title text -
    - Set through styles apptentiveLoveDialogLayoutStyle & apptentiveLoveDialogHeaderImageStyle
    <style name="Custom.LoveDialog.Layout"> <- Override the layout to remove preset paddings
        <item name="android:background">?colorSurface</item> <- Background color of your dialog
    </style>

    <style name="Custom.LoveDialog.HeaderImage">
        <item name="android:src">@drawable/header_image</item> <- Your image
        <item name="android:layout_weight">1</item> <- Weight to make it the entire width of the dialog
        <item name="android:adjustViewBounds">true</item> <- Helps with image resizing
    </style>
    - Love Dialog large header image example end -

    - Love Dialog image buttons example start -
        <style name="Custom.Dialog.Button.Yes" parent="Widget.MaterialComponents.Button.TextButton"> <- TextButton to remove borders
        <item name="android:textSize">0sp</item> <- Get rid of the text
        <item name="android:layout_weight">1</item> <- Let the buttons take up even space
        <item name="android:layout_marginEnd">48dp</item> <- "Yes" is on the right, give it some layout space
        <item name="android:layout_marginStart">24dp</item> <- Spacing from the "no" button
        <item name="android:ambientShadowAlpha">0</item> <- Remove the button shadow color
        <item name="icon">@drawable/yes_image</item> <- Your image for the "Yes" button
        <item name="iconSize">80dp</item> <- Size of your image (use a 1:1 aspect ratio image)
        <item name="iconTint">@null</item> <- Remove the tint layered on top
        <item name="iconGravity">textTop</item> <- Helps with button alignment
        <item name="iconPadding">0dp</item> <- Helps with precise padding around button
        <item name="rippleColor">@null</item> <- Removes button ripple which can look strange with an image
    </style>

    <style name="Custom.Dialog.Button.No" parent="Widget.MaterialComponents.Button.TextButton"> <- TextButton to remove borders
        <item name="android:textSize">0sp</item> <- Get rid of the text
        <item name="android:layout_weight">1</item> <- Let the buttons take up even space
        <item name="android:layout_marginEnd">24dp</item> <- Spacing from the "yes" button
        <item name="android:layout_marginStart">48dp</item> <- "No" is on the left, give it some layout space
        <item name="android:ambientShadowAlpha">0</item> <- Remove the button shadow color
        <item name="icon">@drawable/no_image</item> <- Your image for the "No" button
        <item name="iconSize">80dp</item> <- Size of your image (use a 1:1 aspect ratio image)
        <item name="iconTint">@null</item> <- Remove the tint layered on top
        <item name="iconGravity">textTop</item> <- Helps with button alignment
        <item name="iconPadding">0dp</item> <- Helps with precise padding around button
        <item name="rippleColor">@null</item> <- Removes button ripple which can look strange with an image
    </style>
    - Love Dialog image buttons example start -

    Apptentive Rating Dialog:


    Surveys:
    - Survey toolbar / bottom bar colors uses colorPrimary
    - Survey toolbar / bottom bar text colors uses colorOnPrimary
    - Survey background uses android:colorBackground
    - Survey color on background (text & some widget colors) uses colorOnBackground
    - Survey submit button color uses colorPrimary
    - Survey submit button text color uses colorOnPrimary
    - Survey description, question title, and radio/checkbox options have alphas of .90 by default
        - Override with apptentiveHeaderAlpha
        - Note that affects default text colors as well as error colors
    - Question instructions, text box hints, and range labels have an alpha of .75 by default
        - Override with apptentiveSubheaderAlpha
        - Note that affects default text colors as well as error colors

    Use Survey header image instead of title text:
    - Small Header Example Start -
    - Set through styles apptentiveSurveyTitleStyle & apptentiveSurveyHeaderImageStyle
    - Example (Good starting point):

    <style name="ApptentiveThemeOverride">
        <item name="apptentiveSurveyTitleStyle">@style/Custom.Survey.Title</item>
        <item name="apptentiveSurveyHeaderImageStyle">@style/Custom.Survey.HeaderImage</item>
    </style>

    <style name="Custom.Survey.Title" parent="Widget.MaterialComponents.TextView">
        <item name="android:visibility">gone</item> <- So the title text doesn't show
    </style>

    <style name="Custom.Survey.HeaderImage">
        <item name="android:src">@drawable/small_header_image</item> <- Set your header image here
        <item name="android:maxHeight">?actionBarSize</item> <- minHeight/maxHeight to size
        <item name="android:adjustViewBounds">true</item> <- Helps with image resizing
        <item name="android:layout_gravity">center</item> <- Image positioning
        <item name="android:layout_margin">2dp</item> <- Image spacing
    </style>
    - Small Header Example End -

    - Large Header Example Start -
    - Set through styles apptentiveSurveyTitleStyle & apptentiveSurveyToolbarStyle
    - Example (Good starting point):

    <style name="ApptentiveThemeOverride">
        <item name="apptentiveSurveyTitleStyle">@style/Custom.Survey.Title</item>
        <item name="apptentiveSurveyToolbarStyle">@style/Custom.Survey.Toolbar</item>
    </style>

    <style name="Custom.Survey.Title" parent="Widget.MaterialComponents.TextView">
        <item name="android:visibility">gone</item> <- So the title text doesn't show
    </style>

    <style name="Custom.Survey.Toolbar" parent="Widget.MaterialComponents.Toolbar.Primary">
        <item name="android:background">@drawable/large_header_image</item> <- Set your header image here
        <item name="layout_constraintHeight_max">224dp</item> <- minHeight/maxHeight to size
        <item name="navigationIcon">@drawable/ic_baseline_close_24</item> <- Close navigation icon
        <item name="navigationContentDescription">Close</item> <- Close navigation description
        <item name="navigationIconTint">@android:color/white</item> <- Close navigation color
    </style>
    - Large Header Example End -
    -->

